  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="KT327-kilavi">
        <p type="edition">kiḻavaṉ kēṭkum aṇmaiyaṉāka avaṉ malaiyiṉ iṉṟu ukuvarum yāṟṟiṟku uraippāḷāy
          uraittatu. </p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">Told by her as if telling [something] to the river,
          which comes dropping from his mountain, while HE is near [enough] to hear. </p>
      </div>

      <div xml:id="KT327">
        <lg type="edition">
          <l> nalkiṉ vāḻu nalkūrn tōrvayi</l>
          <l> ṉayaṉila rākuta ṉaṉṟeṉa vuṇarnta</l>
          <l> kuṉṟa nāṭaṉ ṟaṉṉiṉu naṉṟu</l>
          <l> niṉṉilai koṭitāṟ ṟīya kaluḻi</l>
          <l> nammaṉai maṭamaka ḷiṉṉa meṉmaic</l>
          <l> cāyala ḷaḷiya ḷeṉṉāy</l>
          <l> vāḻaitan taṉaiyāṟ cilampupul leṉavē.</l>
        </lg>

        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
          <l>Your attitude [is] cruel indeed, bad muddy water ,</l>
          <l rend="indent">very, more even than [that of] the man from a land of hills himself,</l>
          <l rend="indent">who realised “good [is it] that there are those free from longing,</l>
          <l rend="indent2">for the sake of the poor who live when they are granted</l>
          <l rend="indent8">[something]” .</l>
          <l>Without saying “the inexperienced daughter in our house</l>
          <l rend="indent5">[is] of such soft grace, she [is] pitiable”,</l>
          <l>you have indeed brought banana trees from the mountain side,</l>
          <l rend="indent8">empty .</l>


        </lg>
      </div>
